        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 6 at 4:08AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 407 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from near Dandridge to 13 miles west of Gatlinburg to 16
miles west of Robbinsville. Movement was east at 50 mph. An isolated
thunderstorm may develop in the line of showers.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Stecoah, Smoky Mountains-Newfound Gap, Smoky Mountains-Fontana Area,
Nantahala, Lake Santeetlah, Cheoah, Deals Gap, Fontana Lake, Almond,
and Robbinsville.
</description>
        <instruction>Persons in campgrounds should consider seeking sturdy shelter until
these storms pass.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 AM EDT for western North
Carolina.</instruction>
